cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel model that leverages meta-learning and reweighting techniques, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper also uses an episodic few-shot learning scheme, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks and deep learning, making cs.NE a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on detection within a one-stage architecture suggests that it may also be relevant to robotics and autonomous systems, making cs.RO a possible sub-category.
